-- Lazard Hires BofA's Marc Katz for Global Telecom, Media Investment Banking
-- Serena Saitto
-- 2010-06-14T15:21:54Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-14/lazard-hires-bofa-s-marc-katz-for-global-telecom-media-investment-banking.html

          
          
             Lazard Ltd. , the biggest independent
merger adviser, hired Bank of America Corp.’s  Marc Katz  as
managing director in the global telecommunication, media and
technology investment-banking group.  
 Katz, who will be based in New York, was previously a
managing director in the mergers and acquisitions group of Bank
of America, where he advised media and telecom companies,
Hamilton, Bermuda-based Lazard said today in a statement.  
 Before joining Bank of America in 2008, Katz, 41, was a
media and telecom investment banker at Lehman Brothers Holdings
Inc. for 10 years. He began his career in 1993 as a corporate
lawyer at Weil, Gotshal & Manges LLP.  
 Katz will report to  Woody Young , who joined Lazard last
year as global head of telecommunications and vice chairman of
U.S. investment banking. Katz and Young worked together at Bank
of America and at Lehman.  
 Katz was part of the Lehman team that advised Yahoo! Inc.
in its defense against Microsoft Corp.’s hostile takeover
attempt. Lazard’s TMT group served as adviser to Qwest
Communications International Inc. on its $22.4 billion takeover
by CenturyLink Inc. and  Cisco Systems Inc.  in its $3.16 billion
purchase of Norwegian videoconferencing firm Tandberg ASA.  
